UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 58/EN
1 AN ACT relating to privacy protection.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 189 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Alert" means a notification generated by an ALPR indicating that a
7 vehicle passed an ALPR with a license plate that matches data held by the
8 National Crime Information Center or other comparable database;
9 (b) "Automated license plate reader" or "ALPR" means a system of one (1) or
10 more automated high-speed cameras used in combination with data
11 processing to convert images of vehicles and license plates into computer-
12 readable data;
13 (c) "Captured license plate data" means the vehicle characteristics captured by
14 an ALPR, including the:
15 1. Global positioning system device coordinates;
16 2. Date and time;
17 3. Photographs of the license plate and vehicle;
18 4. License plate number; and
19 5. Vehicle make, model, and color;
20 (d) "Law enforcement agency" has the same meaning as in KRS 61.298;
21 (e) "Public agency" has the same meaning as in KRS 61.870; and
22 (f) "Secured area" means an area, enclosed by clear boundaries, where access
23 is or may be limited.
24 (2) It is unlawful for an individual, entity, partnership, corporation, association, or
25 this Commonwealth, its agencies, and political subdivisions to use an ALPR
26 except as provided in this section.
27 (3) An ALPR may only be deployed or maintained:
Page 1 of 13
HB005820.100 - 14 - XXXX 3/31/2026 12:25 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 58/EN
1 (a) For purposes of:
2 1. Regulating parking;
3 2. Controlling access to secured areas; or
4 3. Promoting public safety, deterring crime, and addressing auto theft;
5 (b) By a public agency or law enforcement agency or its agents solely for
6 purposes of:
7 1. Law enforcement, including but not limited to conducting criminal
8 investigations or ensuring compliance with local, state, or federal law;
9 and
10 2. Commercial vehicle:
11 a. Permitting and credentialing enforcement;
12 b. Safety enforcement and monitoring;
13 c. Violation disputes;
14 d. Compliance investigations;
15 e. Audits; and
16 f. Research for the purpose of applying to commercial vehicle
17 enforcement funding grants; and
18 (c) By the Transportation Cabinet or its agents solely for purposes of:
19 1. Toll collection;
20 2. Road fund revenue collection; and
21 3. Commercial vehicle:
22 a. Permitting and credentialing enforcement;
23 b. Safety enforcement and monitoring;
24 c. Violation disputes;
25 d. Compliance investigations;
26 e. Audits; and
27 f. Research for the purpose of applying to commercial vehicle
Page 2 of 13
HB005820.100 - 14 - XXXX 3/31/2026 12:25 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 58/EN
1 enforcement funding grants.
2 (4) Captured license plate data obtained for a purpose described under this section:
3 (a) Shall not be preserved for more than ninety (90) days unless it:
4 1. Is retained for a lawful purpose described in subsection (3)(b) and (c)
5 of this section;
6 2. Is retained by a law enforcement agency for:
7 a. Use as evidence in a criminal or insurance claim investigation;
8 b. Training purposes, provided that dates, times, and license plate
9 numbers are redacted; or
10 c. Auditing; or
11 3. Has become subject to a subpoena duces tecum or preservation of
12 evidence notification;
13 (b) If the exemption described in paragraph (a)1. of this subsection applies,
14 shall be retained and destroyed in accordance with the applicable agency's
15 record retention policy;
16 (c) Shall only be used by the entity deploying the ALPR, directly for the lawful
17 purposes described in subsection (3) of this section, except as described in
18 paragraph (d) of this subsection; and
19 (d) Shall not be sold, shared, accessed, or transferred for any other purpose,
20 except:
21 1. To a law enforcement officer or agency, or a third-party entity
22 contracted with a law enforcement officer or agency, solely for
23 purposes of protecting public safety or conducting criminal
24 investigations;
25 2. In response to a subpoena duces tecum;
26 3. To the National Insurance Crime Bureau or its successor organization
27 solely for purposes of investigating insurance fraud, assisting in
Page 3 of 13
HB005820.100 - 14 - XXXX 3/31/2026 12:25 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 58/EN
1 vehicle recovery, or adjudicating insurance claims;
2 4. a. To an insurance carrier, its agents, or an insurance support
3 organization solely for purposes of investigating insurance
4 fraud, assisting in vehicle recovery, adjudicating insurance
5 claims, and preventing insurance fraud.
6 b. Notification of potential use of ALPR data shall not be required
7 for vehicle owners who have entered into an insurance contract
8 or submitted an insurance application prior to January 1, 2027.
9 Individuals applying for insurance on or after January 1, 2027,
10 shall be notified by the insurance carrier of the potential use of
11 ALPR data to enforce the contract by either:
12 i. The privacy statement found on the insurance carrier's
13 website;
14 ii. The disclaimer section of the insurance application; or
15 iii. Both;
16 5. a. To a financial institution or its agents or successors solely for
17 purposes of collateral recovery, enforcement of a lien, recovery
18 of defaulted funds, or verification of information provided within
19 a loan application, provided that the vehicle owner has:
20 i. Entered into an agreement or submitted a loan application
21 with the financial institution; or
22 ii. Given written consent to use ALPR data in a binding
23 insurance or financial contract.
24 b. Notification of potential use of ALPR data shall not be required
25 for individuals who have taken an action described in
26 subdivision a.i. or ii. of this subparagraph prior to January 1,
27 2027. Individuals applying for financing on or after January 1,
Page 4 of 13
HB005820.100 - 14 - XXXX 3/31/2026 12:25 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 58/EN
1 2027, shall be notified by the financial institution of the potential
2 use of ALPR data to enforce the contract by either:
3 i. The privacy statement found on the financial institution's
4 website;
5 ii. The disclaimer section of the financing application; or
6 iii. Both; or
7 6. Otherwise in furtherance of the lawful purposes described in
8 subsection (3)(b) and (c) of this section.
9 (5) Prior to the deployment of an ALPR, a law enforcement agency shall adopt and
10 make publicly available a written policy governing the use of the ALPR that
11 includes:
12 (a) A list of databases used to compare with captured license plate data;
13 (b) Rules for retention and destruction of captured license plate data;
14 (c) Training protocol for ALPR systems;
15 (d) Supervisory oversight of the ALPR system;
16 (e) Rules for access to and security of captured license plate data; and
17 (f) An audit schedule and process to ensure that the system is used in
18 accordance with this section and agency policy to occur every ninety (90)
19 days.
20 (6) Upon receipt of an alert and prior to performing a traffic stop, a law enforcement
21 officer or dispatcher shall visually confirm that the:
22 (a) Scanned plate provided in the captured license plate data matches the alert;
23 and
24 (b) Stop meets the criteria in the policies of the law enforcement agency and
25 applicable law.
26 (7) The Transportation Cabinet shall establish a permit process for the installation of
27 ALPR systems on highway rights-of-way and shall promulgate administrative
